COLOR. Body uniformely light brown (
Fig. 24A–B
).

PALP. Tibia with retrolateral conspicuous depression and spines concentrated at basal and apical portions (
Fig. 24C
); embolus with basal torsion and opening of sperm duct in shape of a quill tip (
Fig. 24D–E
).

COLOR. Brown carapace and legs, brownish sternum and coxae (
Fig. 24J–K
), gray abdomen.

PROSOMA. Carapace and ocular arrangement as shown in 
Fig. 24J
. Eye tubercle: 1.2 long; 0.8 wide. AME-ALE distance 1. Eye diameters: AME 0.2, ALE 0.3, PME 0.2, PLE 0.4. Thoracic fovea procurved (
Fig. 24J
). Labium with 2 cuspules (
Fig. 24K
). Maxilla with 48 cuspules, distributed over anterior ventral half, with 6 large cuspules at anterior ventral retrolateral end and 6 large cuspules at anterior ventral prolateral end (
Fig. 24K
). Basal segment of chelicerae with a prolateral row of 7 large teeth and 5 small retrolateral teeth, grouped on basal half, rastellum with 22 short and thick spines (
Fig. 24K
).

SPERMATHECAE. Short and narrow sclerotized base, ducts with same width as receptacles (
Fig. 24L
).
